comments: Morant (MEM) splits his feet at the start of his dribble.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) and Wiggins (GSW) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.

Wiggins (GSW) swipes down and brushes Morant's (MEM) right arm at the end of the drive. Green (GSW) then extends his hand forward as he braces for the impending contact with Morant, which Green absorbs.
Wiggins (GSW) makes contact with the ball and incidental contact with Anderson's (MEM) left hand as they each attempt to retrieve the rebound.

Green (GSW) raises both arms up as Anderson (MEM) jumps toward him and marginal contact occurs with the back of Anderson's head before Green cleanly blocks the shot attempt. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Curry's (GSW) right leg extends forward following the release of his jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Anderson's (MEM) lower half during the follow-through.
Green (GSW) does not bring the ball across half-court within eight seconds.
Iguodala (GSW) and Morant (MEM) engage and disengage with one another as they move over the screen.
Curry (GSW) moves forward toward Melton (MEM) and marginal lower body contact occurs after Melton receives the pass.
Anderson (MEM) establishes himself in a screening position in Curry's (GSW) path and absorbs the contact.
Green (GSW) is late to the spot and does not establish a legal guarding position prior to contact occurring with Anderson (MEM), affecting Anderson's SQBR during the drive.
Morant's (MEM) right hand comes forward toward Curry's (GSW) left shoulder and marginal contact occurs as Morant crosses over.
Wiggins (GSW) and Anderson (MEM) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Curry (GSW) swipes down and makes clean contact with the ball before any incidental contact occurs with Morant (MEM) at the end of the drive.
Green (GSW) cleanly blocks Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) jump shot attempt.
Lee (GSW) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Melton (MEM) before any incidental contact occurs.
Lee (GSW) legally contests Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) jump shot attempt.
Melton (MEM) commits a take foul on Curry (GSW).
Jackson Jr. (MEM) legally contests Curry's (GSW) jump shot attempt and is retreating away from Curry when marginal lower body contact is created by Curry's extended right leg.
Lee (GSW) establishes himself in a screening position in Melton's (MEM) path and absorbs the contact.
Green (GSW) firms up in his screening position in Morant's (MEM) path and absorbs the contact.

Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) right arm comes down as Curry (GSW) begins to drive and marginal contact occurs with the top of Curry's head. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Melton (MEM) jumps forward to contest Green's (GSW) layup attempt and, as Green jumps slightly backward, marginal body contact occurs before Melton cleanly blocks it.
Wiggins (GSW) and Anderson (MEM) each make clean contact with the ball before incidental arm and body contact occurs during rebounding.
Anderson (MEM) grabs and holds Iguodala's (GSW) right arm as he sets the pick, affecting Iguodala's ability to disengage.
Wiggins (GSW) brushes Morant's (MEM) left arm and marginal contact occurs after Morant's gather.
Melton (MEM) briefly has his arms around Green's (GSW) upper half before quickly sliding them off.
Melton (MEM) legally contests Curry's (GSW) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Green (GSW) extends forward and marginal contact occurs with Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) side and left hand after Jackson Jr. hands the ball off.
Lee (GSW) is bringing his arm into a vertical position when marginal contact occurs with Bane's (GSW) left arm after his gather.
Curry (GSW) and Bane (MEM) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Melton's (MEM) arm comes forward toward Curry's (GSW) front and marginal contact occurs as Curry dribbles in transition.
Curry (GSW) swipes his off-arm backward and marginal contact occurs with Melton's (MEM) left arm as Curry starts his dribble.
Bane (MEM) brings his hands to Wiggins' (GSW) sides and marginal contact occurs as Wiggins moves toward the lane line.
Iguodala (GSW) establishes himself in a screening position in Morant's (MEM) path and absorbs the contact.
Iguodala (GSW) commits a take foul on Bane (MEM).
Payton II (GSW) avoids making contact with Morant (MEM) as he attempts to take a foul.
